cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using network coding to optimize video delivery and minimize distortion. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with video streaming and video quality. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses caching and prefetching strategies to relieve strain on backhaul. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on security concerns related to caching and delivery of video content. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possibility as the paper deals with distributed caching and delivery of video content.
